Anyone can implement their own version of any piece. A researcher can plug in a second-order curvature oracle instead of the Fisher-based one. A practitioner can write a custom deployment policy that fits their SLA. The rest of the system works unchanged.

This is what makes MELD infrastructure — not just a paper reimplementation.

